---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Alexandra Kelstrom is a software engineer, responsible AI advocate, and the person behind codewizwit. From bartender to AI enablement leader, this is the story."
>
  <article class="about">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="about-hero section-cream section" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label">About</p>
        <h1 id="about-heading" class="about-title">
          The wiz who came in sideways.
        </h1>
        <p class="about-lede">
          AI Enablement Engineer, responsible AI advocate, and someone who believes
          the most interesting paths are never straight lines.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 1: The Story -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act1-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label label-gold">Act I</p>
        <h2 id="act1-heading">The story</h2>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            With roots in Chicago, I lived in six different countries outside the US. Taiwan, Latvia,
            Czech Republic, England, Scotland, Poland. My father scaled broadband
            infrastructure across Europe and Asia. He built the connective tissue
            that made the internet possible for millions.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm doing the same for AI: building the ethical and practical
            frameworks that will determine whether it serves people or replaces them.
          </p>
          <p>
            I studied Media and Design at DePaul University in Chicago. I
            bartended for years. The service industry taught me empathy as an
            operational skill: reading people, understanding needs, solving
            problems in real-time. Those skills transferred to engineering more
            directly than any CS lecture could.
          </p>
          <p>
            Then COVID hit. I got furloughed. I invested my life savings in
            the UPenn LPS Coding Bootcamp. I received my offer at Vanguard the
            day I graduated.
          </p>
          <p>
            That pivot wasn't reckless. It was a calculated bet on myself. And
            it paid off.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 2: The Work -->
    <section class="section-dark section" aria-labelledby="act2-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label" style="color: var(--color-gray-light);">Act II</p>
        <h2 id="act2-heading" style="color: var(--color-cream);">The work</h2>
        <div class="prose" style="color: var(--color-gray-light);">
          <p>
            At Vanguard, I coach four teams on AI adoption, mentor junior
            engineers, and drive culture with a responsible AI lens. I
            build the tools and frameworks that help people use AI without
            losing what makes their work human.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before that, I was writing automated tests, building component
            libraries, and pushing for developer experience improvements
            that nobody asked for but everyone needed. Quality is care
            made visible. That hasn't changed.
          </p>
          <p>
            The throughline from bartending to engineering to AI enablement
            is the same: read the room, understand what people actually
            need, and build something that serves them. The tools changed.
            The instinct didn't.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Hot Dog -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="hot-dog-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="hot-dog-heading" class="hot-dog-section-title">
          And yes, <a href="/the-hot-dog" class="link">the hot dog is a whole thing.</a>
        </h2>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Act 3: Beyond the Code -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="act3-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="label">Act III</p>
        <h2 id="act3-heading">Beyond the code</h2>
        <div class="beyond-grid">
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Soundtrack</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Huge music nerd. Soul, jazz, rock, oldies, reggae, indie. Hip-hop and doo-wop are my favorites. Always loud.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fuel</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Good meals start the best conversations. Great snacks start the best ideas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Fiction</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Sci-fi. Always pondering the future we're building.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Eye</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">DePaul Media &amp; Design grad. Visual thinker solving technical problems.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Superpower</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">Empathy. Understanding people, anticipating needs, and turning that into strategic problem solving. The bartender instinct never left.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beyond-item">
            <h3 class="beyond-label">Roots</h3>
            <p class="beyond-text">
              With roots in Chicago, I lived in six different countries outside the US.
              Dual citizen (US + Czech Republic). Philadelphia is currently where I call home.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-lede {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .about h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .hot-dog-section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  }

  .about .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-hover);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a {
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .section-dark .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .beyond-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .beyond-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .beyond-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
  }

  .beyond-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .about-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-gold-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about-inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold-hover);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .beyond-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
